---
title: Grilled Parmesan Burgers with Rosemary Garlic Mayonnaise and Lemon Butter Corn
description: Summertime cooking is all about embracing the thrill of the grill. Which means that this recipe is a thriller, all right, since it features beef patties, onion, and tomato all cooked over the flames and tucked into a brioche bun. Even the corn on the cob on the side is left to get a little charred on the grates, so every single bite has smoky flavor. P.S.: If your grill is still on winter break, no worries—these burgers can also be made in a pan.
