> Summertime cooking is all about embracing the thrill of the grill. Which means that
> this recipe is a thriller, all right, since it features beef patties, onion, and
> tomato all cooked over the flames and tucked into a brioche bun. Even the corn on
> the cob on the side is left to get a little charred on the grates, so every single
> bite has smoky flavor. P.S.: If your grill is still on winter break, no worries—
> these burgers can also be made in a pan.

Wash and dry all produce. If grilling, heat a #grill{} for direct heat. Zest @lemon{1} 1 tsp zest from lemon, then cut in half. Squeeze 2 tsp juice into a #small bowl{}. Strip and finely chop enough @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems to give you 1 TBSP. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} in another small, #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave on high until just soft, about ~{10%seconds}. (TIP: Make sure not to melt butter.) Stir in lemon zest, @sugar{¼%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside. To bowl with reserved lemon juice, add @mayonnaise{6%tablespoon}, a pinch of garlic, 1 tsp rosemary, and a pinch of @pepper{pinch}. Stir to combine.

Slice @tomato{1} into ⅓- to ½-inch-thick rounds. Peel @red onion{1}, then slice into ½-inch-thick rounds. Carefully cut or break @corn on the cob{2} ears in half. Place @ground beef{20%ounce}, @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, remaining garlic and rosemary, a pinch of pepper, and a few large pinches of salt in a #large bowl{}. Mix until just combined, then shape into four 4-inch-wide patties.

Brush grill grates with @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. (TIP: If cooking indoors, heat a drizzle of olive oil in two #grill pans{} or large pans over medium-high heat; use one for the veggies in this step and use the other for the patties.) Add corn and cook, turning occasionally, until charred all over, about ~{10%minutes}. Add onion rounds and cook until charred, about ~{3%minutes} per side. Add tomato and cook until charred, about ~{2%minutes} per side.

Add patties to grill or other pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. If you'd like toasted buns, split @brioche buns{4} in half and grill cut-side down until light golden, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Spread buns with mayonnaise mixture and fill with patties, tomato, and onion. Dollop corn with butter mixture and serve on the side.